{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 21:19:35.250308", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report — SDN Spine–Leaf Lab\n\nSummary\n- Network health: Critical outage affecting the entire data-plane. No L2 connectivity between any hosts, including those on the same leaf.\n- Primary anomaly: ARP resolution fails across the 10.0.0.0/24 host network; all pings result in “Destination Host Unreachable.”\n- Fault localization: All Open vSwitch (OVS) devices (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) are non-functional as switches.\n- Probable root cause: OVS switching services are inactive (dead) on all switches while configured in fail_mode=secure with a controller target. This results in zero forwarding and ARP flooding suppression, causing pervasive L2 failure.\n\nKey Findings\n\n1) End-to-end reachability (hosts)\n- Failures within the same leaf:\n  - host_1_1 -> host_1_2: Destination Host Unreachable (100% loss).\n  - host_2_1 -> host_2_2: Destination Host Unreachable (100% loss).\n- Failures across leaves:\n  - host_1_1 -> host_2_1 and host_2_1 -> host_1_2: Destination Host Unreachable (100% loss).\n\nInterpretation: Even intra-leaf L2 forwarding is down. This strongly implicates the leaf switches (leaf_1, leaf_2).\n\n2) ARP behavior on hosts\n- Example from host_1_1 (cat /proc/net/arp):\n  - Entries for peers show flags 0x0 (incomplete), MAC 00:00:00:00:00:00.\nInterpretation: ARP requests are not being answered/flooded, consistent with a non-forwarding L2 fabric.\n\n3) Switch status and configuration\n- OVS service state:\n  - openvswitch-switch on leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1: “Active: inactive (dead)”.\n- OVS configuration (ovs-vsctl show) exists on each switch:\n  - Bridges defined (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1).\n  - Controller set to tcp:20.0.0.100:6633.\n  - fail_mode: secure.\n- Interface state:\n  - Data-plane NICs are enslaved to OVS (master ovs-system).\n  - RX counters increment slightly; TX counters at 0 on several ports, indicating no forwarding.\n\nInterpretation: The OVS database retains bridge/port/controller configuration, but the switching daemon(s) are not active. With fail_mode=secure and no active controller session, OVS drops all traffic rather than performing standalone MAC learning or flooding.\n\n4) Controller reachability (management network)\n- All switches can ping the controller IP 20.0.0.100 successfully.\nInterpretation: The management network is healthy, and basic IP connectivity to the controller host exists. The lack of forwarding is not due to management reachability loss. However, there is no evidence of an active OpenFlow connection from the switches (and OVS is inactive).\n\nLocalization\n- leaf_1: Fails to switch between directly attached hosts (host_1_1, host_1_2). OVS service inactive. Fault confirmed at the leaf.\n- leaf_2: Same symptom with host_2_1 and host_2_2. OVS service inactive. Fault confirmed at the leaf.\n- spine_1: Also shows OVS service inactive. While intra-leaf traffic doesn’t require the spine, the spine would be required for inter-leaf connectivity; its non-functional state contributes to broader failure.\n- Controller host (20.0.0.100): Reachable via ICMP; however, no evidence here confirms an active OpenFlow controller process or switch connections. Regardless, with OVS daemons inactive, the switches cannot participate even if a controller is available.\n\nRoot Cause Assessment\n- Immediate root cause: Open vSwitch is not running on all switching nodes (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1), as evidenced by systemd status “inactive (dead).” This disables the data-plane and prevents ARP flooding and L2 forwarding.\n- Contributing factor: The switches are configured with fail_mode=secure and a controller target at 20.0.0.100. In secure mode, when a controller is not connected, OVS drops traffic. With OVS itself inactive, there can be no controller connection or flow programming.\n- Net effect: Complete loss of layer-2 forwarding across the fabric, resulting in ARP failures and “Destination Host Unreachable” from all hosts in 10.0.0.0/24.\n\nImpact\n- All hosts in 10.0.0.0/24 are isolated; intra-leaf and inter-leaf communication fail.\n- Management network (20.0.0.0/24) remains reachable among switches and the controller host.\n\nSupporting Evidence (selected)\n- Ping failures:\n  - host_1_1 -> 10.0.0.2: “Destination Host Unreachable” (100% loss).\n  - host_1_1 -> 10.0.0.5: “Destination Host Unreachable” (100% loss).\n  - host_2_1 -> 10.0.0.6: “Destination Host Unreachable” (100% loss).\n- ARP on host_1_1:\n  - Flags 0x0 for peers, MAC 00:00:00:00:00:00 (incomplete).\n- OVS service on switches:\n  - “Active: inactive (dead)” on leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1.\n- OVS configuration:\n  - Bridges present with “Controller tcp:20.0.0.100:6633” and “fail_mode: secure.”\n- Management ping:\n  - leaf_1/leaf_2/spine_1 -> 20.0.0.100: 0% loss, sub-ms RTTs.\n\nConclusion\nThe network is experiencing a complete L2 forwarding outage due to inactive Open vSwitch processes on all switches. With fail_mode=secure and absent controller connectivity/flows, no traffic is forwarded, ARP fails, and all host communications in 10.0.0.0/24 are down. The issue is localized to the switching layer (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1). The management plane is healthy.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 15803, "output_tokens": 3584, "total_tokens": 19387, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 15488}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 2240}}}
